#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""x-ingest — pull curated X (Twitter) watchlist into ~/brain/ as electrification
thesis signals.

Source of truth for watchlist: ~/bin/config/x-watchlist.json (26 accounts in
3 tiers as of 2026-05-20). Edit the JSON; the collector reconciles against
its private X List at run start.

Architecture (hybrid):
  --backfill : per-handle pulls via GET /2/users/{id}/tweets, tiered window
               (T1=90d, T2=30d, T3=7d). One-time.
  --delta    : (default) Lists API pull via GET /2/lists/{id}/tweets, paginated,
               since last watermark. Falls back to per-handle if List endpoint
               errors. 2x/wk via brain-run Phase 7.
  --setup    : create the private X List from the watchlist; write list_id back
               into x-watchlist.json. Runs once at install.

Signal filter:
  - thesis-keyword match (THESIS_KEYWORDS)
  - engagement gate: T1 = any post; T2/T3 = author-normalized z-score
    (median + IQR), n>=15 author baseline required; absolute-threshold fallback
    during backfill or for accounts below the baseline floor.
  - thread-starter T1 posts pass without engagement
  - cross-watchlist mention always passes

Two-write pattern (transactional):
  1. signal page at ~/brain/signals/YYYY-MM/<handle>-<post-id>.md
  2. people timeline at ~/brain/people/<slug>.md  (append at ## Timeline)
  Cursor advances only after both succeed. Failed people-write → reconcile queue.

Narrative tracking: 3+ posts with >=2 keyword overlap AND >=1 rare keyword in
7d window per handle -> annotate compiled truth with `expires: +90d` TTL.

Auth: X_BEARER_TOKEN in macOS keychain. Cron fallback: ~/.gbrain/secrets.env.
  security add-generic-password -a "$USER" -s X_BEARER_TOKEN -w '<token>'

This script does not call brain-sync. brain-run --with-x invokes it as Phase 7.

Schema: x-watchlist.json schema_version=1.
"""
